<p>We believe in a system that displays the utmost confidence in every student to grow, as a scholar and as a person.</p>

<p>Therefore, we have worked to create a student-based system where our tutors will help students learn the skills they need to thrive in this century.  Not just “reading, writing, ‘rithmetic” — but also computer literacy and other important skills (this clause may be amended).  And we will also help them teach others - from their peers to the next generations - these skills.  After all, as the philosopher Joseph Joubert said, “To teach is to learn twice.”</p>

<p>We hope to instill a better sense of citizenship and service not just in our students, but also in the people and communities whom they inspire. </p>

